WEBVTT

1
00:00:03.000 --> 00:00:04.716
<i>- Previously on tracker...
- Hey. you got a sec?</i>

2
00:00:04.740 --> 00:00:06.820
- Yeah. What's up?
- Need you to look into somebody.

3
00:00:11.750 --> 00:00:13.710
I'm looking for witnesses
to testify in a lawsuit.

4
00:00:19.670 --> 00:00:21.540
Everyone else broke but not me.

5
00:00:21.720 --> 00:00:24.126
What happened when you said no?

6
00:00:24.150 --> 00:00:26.500
They made me look insane.

7
00:00:26.640 --> 00:00:30.730
When everyone started
believing them. I did feel nuts.

8
00:00:30.860 --> 00:00:34.170
You know you don't need to
fight this alone anymore. right?

9
00:00:34.300 --> 00:00:36.350
I can't erase what that company did.

10
00:00:37.730 --> 00:00:39.780
But I can make them answer for it.

11
00:02:13.790 --> 00:02:15.660
<i>You still can't reach him?</i>

12
00:02:15.790 --> 00:02:17.970
He should've been
here over two hours ago.

13
00:02:18.090 --> 00:02:19.856
- It's not like kurtis.
- Well. there's a lot of pressure

14
00:02:19.880 --> 00:02:21.580
right before trial. right?

15
00:02:21.710 --> 00:02:23.466
It's not the first time I've
seen a witness spook.

16
00:02:23.490 --> 00:02:24.930
He's only missed one prep meeting.

17
00:02:26.930 --> 00:02:29.630
- Maybe I should go check on him.
- Well. I'm right by his house.

18
00:02:29.760 --> 00:02:31.720
If it makes you feel
better. I'll swing by. okay?

19
00:02:31.800 --> 00:02:33.320
Yeah.

20
00:02:53.830 --> 00:02:55.270
Kurtis?

21
00:03:28.510 --> 00:03:29.510
Hey. Any luck?

22
00:03:29.640 --> 00:03:31.536
<i>I'm at his house.</i>

23
00:03:31.560 --> 00:03:33.056
I think you were right.
Something's wrong.

24
00:03:33.080 --> 00:03:35.340
Why? What'd you see?

25
00:03:35.480 --> 00:03:37.400
<i>Well. his truck's not here.</i>

26
00:03:37.520 --> 00:03:40.920
but his phone's in there
and his oxygen tank.

27
00:03:41.050 --> 00:03:42.400
<i>There's just no sign of him.</i>

28
00:03:42.570 --> 00:03:44.066
<i>I could try to get in. I guess. but...</i>

29
00:03:44.090 --> 00:03:46.530
No. no. no. no. Don't touch anything.

30
00:03:46.660 --> 00:03:47.816
<i>You're right. I'm gonna call the police.</i>

31
00:03:47.840 --> 00:03:49.620
Not yet.

32
00:03:49.750 --> 00:03:51.880
If he's missing. I know who to call.

33
00:04:09.600 --> 00:04:11.536
He's been missing seven hours at least.

34
00:04:11.560 --> 00:04:13.480
He was scheduled to testify tomorrow.

35
00:04:15.520 --> 00:04:17.780
What's this? I got a phone over here.

36
00:04:19.560 --> 00:04:21.430
It's dead.

37
00:04:21.570 --> 00:04:23.366
You get Randy looking for his truck?

38
00:04:23.390 --> 00:04:26.026
Yeah. couldn't find anything. No GPS.

39
00:04:26.050 --> 00:04:27.410
We called all the local hospitals.

40
00:04:31.790 --> 00:04:33.776
make it happen.

41
00:04:33.800 --> 00:04:36.460
Colter. this is Maxine.

42
00:04:36.580 --> 00:04:38.380
Maxine. how you doing?
Heard a lot about you.

43
00:04:42.410 --> 00:04:44.590
Were you able to reach the judge?

44
00:04:48.240 --> 00:04:50.680
But I didn't want to say too
much until we were face to face.

45
00:04:53.510 --> 00:04:54.950
What could have happened to kurtis?

46
00:04:55.080 --> 00:04:56.690
Well. worst case?

47
00:04:56.820 --> 00:05:00.040
Praiter and Rockwell or someone
connected to the case took him.

48
00:05:00.170 --> 00:05:02.520
Is there evidence backing that up?

49
00:05:02.650 --> 00:05:04.016
I mean. the case has
been really weird so far.

50
00:05:04.040 --> 00:05:08.480
Packages were delivered
to my office. Maxine's as well.

51
00:05:08.610 --> 00:05:10.400
Surveillance footage of us at home.

52
00:05:10.530 --> 00:05:11.580
At home?

53
00:05:11.700 --> 00:05:13.700
I know.

54
00:05:13.840 --> 00:05:16.710
Right after we made
a new claim to the suit.

55
00:05:16.840 --> 00:05:19.280
And kurtis's testimony
was key to proving it.

56
00:05:19.410 --> 00:05:22.060
If we win. it could be
fatal to the company.

57
00:05:22.190 --> 00:05:23.686
You let the police know
about these threats?

58
00:05:23.710 --> 00:05:25.670
No. Didn't rise to it.

59
00:05:28.200 --> 00:05:30.030
Well. there's something here.

60
00:05:31.070 --> 00:05:32.900
I think it's blood.

61
00:05:33.030 --> 00:05:34.160
Wait. what?

62
00:05:34.290 --> 00:05:36.070
Yeah. There was more.

63
00:05:36.210 --> 00:05:39.470
Someone tried to clean
it up. missed a spot.

64
00:05:43.210 --> 00:05:44.860
On the counter next to you.

65
00:05:46.740 --> 00:05:48.050
Here's what I'm thinking.

66
00:05:48.170 --> 00:05:51.260
I'm thinking our guy.
he. came in here. right?

67
00:05:51.390 --> 00:05:53.220
Hid himself in this pantry.

68
00:05:53.350 --> 00:05:55.546
They ambushed kurtis.

69
00:05:55.570 --> 00:05:57.610
Now. it was somebody who
knew what they were doing.

70
00:06:04.890 --> 00:06:06.850
I pushed him into doing the lawsuit.

71
00:06:06.980 --> 00:06:09.020
It's not your fault. You're
doing your job. reenie.

72
00:06:10.630 --> 00:06:13.110
They went this way.

73
00:06:13.290 --> 00:06:15.160
- I think that's the judge.
- You go ahead.

74
00:07:06.990 --> 00:07:08.926
Yeah. that's not kurtis.-.

75
00:07:08.950 --> 00:07:11.300
It's the intruder... maybe
one of them anyway.

76
00:07:11.430 --> 00:07:12.910
This guy was stabbed.

77
00:07:13.040 --> 00:07:16.040
- Explains the blood inside.
- Yeah. What are you thinking?

78
00:07:17.870 --> 00:07:18.936
Kills him with the knife?

79
00:07:18.960 --> 00:07:20.936
I mean. he's an elderly man.

80
00:07:20.960 --> 00:07:22.440
He uses intermittent oxygen.

81
00:07:23.830 --> 00:07:26.490
What about the missing truck?

82
00:07:26.620 --> 00:07:28.840
I'm not so sure.

83
00:07:28.970 --> 00:07:30.776
Someone was trying to
cover this up though. right?

84
00:07:30.800 --> 00:07:32.520
I'm thinking maybe
there was a third party.

85
00:07:32.580 --> 00:07:35.450
Maybe they-they took
kurtis in his own truck.

86
00:07:38.020 --> 00:07:40.590
If they killed him. we would've
found his body already.

87
00:07:44.640 --> 00:07:46.640
Well. they got sloppy.

88
00:07:46.770 --> 00:07:48.446
If they made more
mistakes. I'll see them.

89
00:07:48.470 --> 00:07:50.170
Okay. Maxine's on her way to the office.

90
00:07:50.300 --> 00:07:52.260
She'll handle the legal
side. I'll call the cops.

91
00:07:52.430 --> 00:07:54.780
Colter. you got to find this guy for me.

92
00:07:54.910 --> 00:07:56.390
Yeah.

93
00:07:56.560 --> 00:07:58.480
I'm on it.

94
00:08:00.350 --> 00:08:02.570
<i>Randy. you get any
new hits on kurtis's truck?</i>

95
00:08:02.700 --> 00:08:04.010
Nada.

96
00:08:04.140 --> 00:08:06.580
I'm monitoring traffic cams. toll roads.

97
00:08:11.580 --> 00:08:12.970
I didn't see the radio anywhere.

98
00:08:13.100 --> 00:08:15.256
I'm thinking maybe he
installed it in his truck.

99
00:08:15.280 --> 00:08:17.200
Sending you a photo right now.

100
00:08:17.320 --> 00:08:18.710
<i>It has the ham's call sign.</i>

101
00:08:18.850 --> 00:08:20.590
I like it. Let me see.

102
00:08:31.120 --> 00:08:32.950
Pla-dow. there it is.

103
00:08:35.910 --> 00:08:37.610
<i>Got it.</i>

104
00:08:37.730 --> 00:08:39.430
<i>Hey. listen. Randy.</i>

105
00:08:40.960 --> 00:08:42.530
Reenie mentioned something about.

106
00:08:46.660 --> 00:08:48.100
<i>dropped off a package.</i>

107
00:08:48.220 --> 00:08:49.596
Could have something to
do with what happened here.

108
00:08:49.620 --> 00:08:51.100
Yeah. no doubt.

109
00:08:51.230 --> 00:08:53.060
I'm working to beef up security though.

110
00:08:53.180 --> 00:08:54.206
Did you get an ID?

111
00:08:54.230 --> 00:08:55.540
<i>Not yet.</i>

112
00:08:55.670 --> 00:08:57.500
Mel took a great photo.

113
00:09:02.980 --> 00:09:03.980
You got it. man.

114
00:09:07.940 --> 00:09:09.826
But nobody recognized
the courier from the photo.

115
00:09:09.850 --> 00:09:11.330
That's okay. Thank you for this.

116
00:09:11.460 --> 00:09:13.590
If I'd gotten my phone out sooner.

117
00:09:13.730 --> 00:09:14.730
taken a better picture...

118
00:09:14.820 --> 00:09:16.780
Come on. This is not your fault.

119
00:09:16.900 --> 00:09:19.730
Just worried about reenie.

120
00:09:19.860 --> 00:09:21.990
We really got to find the guy who did this.

121
00:09:22.130 --> 00:09:23.650
Mel...

122
00:09:25.610 --> 00:09:27.350
You know I got you. right?

123
00:09:44.110 --> 00:09:46.166
The circumstances are
beyond our control. your honor.

124
00:09:46.190 --> 00:09:48.110
- We need more time.
- So your whole case

125
00:09:48.280 --> 00:09:49.890
hinges on this witness's testimony?

126
00:09:50.070 --> 00:09:51.510
Give me a break. hoover.

127
00:09:51.630 --> 00:09:53.110
You know damn well hundreds of people

128
00:09:53.290 --> 00:09:55.770
have signed onto this lawsuit
condemning praiter and Rockwell.

129
00:09:59.820 --> 00:10:02.446
And I'm guessing their client
does as well. and here we are.

130
00:10:02.470 --> 00:10:04.340
And where is that exactly?

131
00:10:04.520 --> 00:10:06.960
You can't produce your witness.
It's not exactly our problem.

132
00:10:11.000 --> 00:10:13.570
Possibly worse.

133
00:10:13.700 --> 00:10:16.790
That's a pretty strong
accusation. counsel.

134
00:10:16.920 --> 00:10:19.156
Do you have any
evidence to substantiate it?

135
00:10:19.180 --> 00:10:21.400
A police report? Missing
persons complaint?

136
00:10:21.530 --> 00:10:23.650
We are actively investigating
the matter. your honor.

137
00:10:25.060 --> 00:10:27.386
He probably changed
his mind and ghosted you.

138
00:10:27.410 --> 00:10:30.590
Did you two rehearse this little
back-and-forth pantomime thing?

139
00:10:30.720 --> 00:10:32.176
We remain ready to meet
the trial date. your honor.

140
00:10:32.200 --> 00:10:33.640
All we are asking for.

141
00:10:41.420 --> 00:10:42.926
Or your client out of the loop. Devin.

142
00:10:42.950 --> 00:10:44.740
I know they are so concerned.

143
00:10:44.860 --> 00:10:45.910
That's enough. Ms. Greene.

144
00:10:46.950 --> 00:10:49.170
You have 24 hours.

145
00:10:49.300 --> 00:10:50.430
Use them wisely.

146
00:10:50.560 --> 00:10:52.610
Thank you. your honor.

147
00:11:02.270 --> 00:11:04.556
Praiter and Rockwell
kidnapped a witness.

148
00:11:04.580 --> 00:11:06.970
Actually. yes.

149
00:11:07.100 --> 00:11:09.946
Well. now I'm looking forward to trial.

150
00:11:09.970 --> 00:11:12.670
We welcome baseless allegations.

151
00:11:12.850 --> 00:11:14.630
Be sure to work those into your cross.

152
00:11:14.760 --> 00:11:18.006
You should be looking
forward to my advice: Buckle up.

153
00:11:18.030 --> 00:11:19.730
I hope you didn't take this personally.

154
00:11:19.850 --> 00:11:22.226
Just business. right?

155
00:11:22.250 --> 00:11:24.820
I can assure you our
client had nothing to do with

156
00:11:29.780 --> 00:11:32.220
now we've threatened you
in addition to your witness.

157
00:11:32.340 --> 00:11:34.326
How about we just table
this until trial. shall we?

158
00:11:34.350 --> 00:11:37.870
Let's go.

159
00:11:40.050 --> 00:11:41.920
Hey. let's. let's go ahead and lock down

160
00:11:42.050 --> 00:11:44.310
the other witnesses.
make sure they're protected.

161
00:11:44.440 --> 00:11:47.010
Got it. You focus on kurtis. You
know him better than anyone.

162
00:11:47.140 --> 00:11:48.776
Yeah.

163
00:11:48.800 --> 00:11:50.850
Thanks for having my back.

164
00:11:50.970 --> 00:11:52.230
Thank you.

165
00:13:10.790 --> 00:13:11.920
Okay.

166
00:13:18.620 --> 00:13:20.230
Found the truck. It's totaled.

167
00:13:20.360 --> 00:13:22.060
- Kurtis?
- No sign

168
00:13:22.190 --> 00:13:24.190
<i>that anyone was in the
truck when it crashed.</i>

169
00:13:28.980 --> 00:13:30.500
They wanted us to think they ran.

170
00:13:30.640 --> 00:13:32.950
Okay. So now what?

171
00:13:33.070 --> 00:13:35.186
Looks like you'd need a car from here.

172
00:13:35.210 --> 00:13:37.690
so either they stashed one
or maybe they stole one.

173
00:13:37.860 --> 00:13:39.500
All right. look. you've got me and Randy.

174
00:13:39.600 --> 00:13:41.470
I'm gonna put you on speaker.

175
00:13:41.600 --> 00:13:42.990
Hey. what's up. man?

176
00:13:43.170 --> 00:13:44.186
Randy. any records of a stolen vehicle

177
00:13:44.210 --> 00:13:45.496
anywhere near my location?

178
00:13:45.520 --> 00:13:47.090
Let's find out.

179
00:13:48.780 --> 00:13:50.196
Nope. nothing reported today.

180
00:13:50.220 --> 00:13:51.766
All right.

181
00:13:51.790 --> 00:13:54.230
Passed a roadhouse
about a half a mile back.

182
00:13:54.360 --> 00:13:56.450
<i>And a motel. Looked like
the last stop within miles.</i>

183
00:13:58.490 --> 00:13:59.970
Yeah. I see it.

184
00:14:00.100 --> 00:14:01.946
Looks like the perfect place to get a car.

185
00:14:01.970 --> 00:14:03.866
<i>- Or to sit and wait in one.
- That's what I'm thinking.</i>

186
00:14:03.890 --> 00:14:05.570
Can you check to see
if they have cameras?

187
00:14:08.410 --> 00:14:10.046
<i>- If they do. they're air-gapped.
- I'm not seeing anything.</i>

188
00:14:10.070 --> 00:14:11.390
All right. I'm heading there now.

189
00:14:11.460 --> 00:14:13.770
Maybe someone saw
something. Thanks.

190
00:14:59.120 --> 00:15:01.210
- Excuse me.
- Hey. man.

191
00:15:01.340 --> 00:15:02.836
Nothing wrong with day drinking.

192
00:15:02.860 --> 00:15:04.486
It's just. we got this thing called hours.

193
00:15:04.510 --> 00:15:07.016
No. I'm not... I'm not here for the bar.

194
00:15:07.040 --> 00:15:08.796
I was wondering maybe you
could help me with something.

195
00:15:08.820 --> 00:15:10.520
I'm. looking for this guy.

196
00:15:10.650 --> 00:15:11.740
He's missing.

197
00:15:11.870 --> 00:15:13.310
Seen him?

198
00:15:14.610 --> 00:15:16.960
I wasn't working last
night. Nothing today.

199
00:15:17.090 --> 00:15:19.010
Why are you looking for him?

200
00:15:19.140 --> 00:15:21.140
It's sort of what I do. Find people.

201
00:15:21.270 --> 00:15:23.790
Sounds mysterious.

202
00:15:23.920 --> 00:15:26.166
It can be. Yeah. Yeah.

203
00:15:26.190 --> 00:15:27.840
Your. your security footage.

204
00:15:27.970 --> 00:15:29.946
is there a chance I could
get a look at that maybe?

205
00:15:29.970 --> 00:15:31.410
Yeah. I don't know.

206
00:15:31.540 --> 00:15:33.260
I might have to run
that one by my manager.

207
00:15:39.200 --> 00:15:41.990
You help me. I help you?

208
00:15:44.810 --> 00:15:46.550
- Hand it over.
- Great.

209
00:15:53.080 --> 00:15:54.780
Wow. you made that look really easy.

210
00:15:54.950 --> 00:15:56.560
It's not my first time.

211
00:15:56.690 --> 00:16:00.456
All right. now... Password.

212
00:16:00.480 --> 00:16:02.440
Right. I really shouldn't be doing this.

213
00:16:02.570 --> 00:16:04.660
Probably not.

214
00:16:14.800 --> 00:16:16.590
Keep going.

215
00:16:19.630 --> 00:16:21.020
Okay. that's him.

216
00:16:21.200 --> 00:16:23.476
Damn.

217
00:16:23.500 --> 00:16:25.110
What's the deal with this guy anyway?

218
00:16:25.250 --> 00:16:26.560
Is he in trouble?

219
00:16:26.680 --> 00:16:28.860
Something like that. yeah.

220
00:16:28.990 --> 00:16:30.576
Pause it right there. will you?

221
00:16:30.600 --> 00:16:32.650
Thank you.

222
00:16:36.950 --> 00:16:39.520
- Grandpa just boosted that car.
- Yeah.

223
00:16:42.310 --> 00:16:44.830
One sec. Hold on. That
SUV. you recognize that?

224
00:16:45.000 --> 00:16:47.610
Nope. But it looks shady as hell.

225
00:16:47.750 --> 00:16:49.800
It does. doesn't it?

226
00:16:49.920 --> 00:16:52.026
Okay. Got what I needed.
Well. thank you very. very much.

227
00:16:52.050 --> 00:16:53.376
- I appreciate you.
- You're welcome.

228
00:16:53.400 --> 00:16:54.580
All right.

229
00:16:54.710 --> 00:16:56.490
Hey.

230
00:16:56.620 --> 00:16:58.320
Come back anytime.

231
00:17:01.930 --> 00:17:03.980
Thanks again.

232
00:17:05.500 --> 00:17:06.940
Hey. You've got me and Randy.

233
00:17:11.470 --> 00:17:12.630
Didn't look to me like it was

234
00:17:12.730 --> 00:17:14.096
the first time he had ever done that.

235
00:17:14.120 --> 00:17:15.486
<i>Sent you a picture of the car he stole</i>

236
00:17:15.510 --> 00:17:17.510
<i>from a security cam at the bar.</i>

237
00:17:17.650 --> 00:17:19.536
- Who is this guy?
- I don't know.

238
00:17:19.560 --> 00:17:21.496
He killed somebody in self-defense.

239
00:17:21.520 --> 00:17:23.170
Doesn't call the police. He covers it up.

240
00:17:23.300 --> 00:17:25.910
<i>Ditches his car. steals another.</i>

241
00:17:26.090 --> 00:17:28.010
<i>Does he have criminal history?</i>

242
00:17:28.130 --> 00:17:30.050
Man. I did a background
check on this guy twice.

243
00:17:32.570 --> 00:17:35.310
High school education.
divorced. one stepdaughter.

244
00:17:39.930 --> 00:17:41.336
Maybe we're not the
only ones on his trail.

245
00:17:41.360 --> 00:17:43.060
Did you run the plates
on that stolen car?

246
00:17:44.410 --> 00:17:46.190
Okay.

247
00:17:46.330 --> 00:17:47.850
Plates on the stolen car pop up twice.

248
00:17:47.940 --> 00:17:49.786
both times on the highway.

249
00:17:49.810 --> 00:17:51.810
<i>The first hit's a toll on the e-470.</i>

250
00:17:51.940 --> 00:17:53.330
The second was him merging onto

251
00:17:53.510 --> 00:17:56.080
the i-70 mountain Lane
express this morning.

252
00:17:56.210 --> 00:17:58.210
And nothing since then.

253
00:17:58.380 --> 00:18:00.226
Maybe the person following
him ran him off the road.

254
00:18:00.250 --> 00:18:02.510
Or maybe he gave
them the slip. All right.

255
00:18:04.000 --> 00:18:06.130
Police identified the
body from kurtis's house.

256
00:18:06.300 --> 00:18:07.536
He worked for a trucking company.

257
00:18:07.560 --> 00:18:10.130
He's got a rap sheet for assault. robbery.

258
00:18:14.830 --> 00:18:16.116
Dude keeps a pretty tight circle.

259
00:18:16.140 --> 00:18:18.816
Only people he talks to are

260
00:18:18.840 --> 00:18:21.800
his stepdaughter Jackie
and his ex-wife Sienna.

261
00:18:21.930 --> 00:18:23.556
When's the last time
they were in contact?

262
00:18:23.580 --> 00:18:26.190
The stepdaughter. a few weeks ago.

263
00:18:26.370 --> 00:18:27.630
The ex-wife. yesterday morning.

264
00:18:27.760 --> 00:18:30.370
Maybe she knows
something. I'll pay her a visit.

265
00:19:55.460 --> 00:19:57.510
Are you one of lowell's men?

266
00:19:58.890 --> 00:20:00.280
How did you find me?

267
00:20:02.110 --> 00:20:06.120
I said. how did you find me?!

268
00:20:34.060 --> 00:20:35.150
You hear me. kurtis.

269
00:20:35.280 --> 00:20:36.980
Lowell ain't gonna stop until you're dead.

270
00:21:10.440 --> 00:21:12.090
Why don't you tell me who you really are.

271
00:21:24.460 --> 00:21:25.956
Reenie Greene.

272
00:21:25.980 --> 00:21:28.720
My name's colter Shaw.
She hired me to come find you.

273
00:21:32.940 --> 00:21:34.250
How's that feel?

274
00:21:34.380 --> 00:21:36.470
You got a high ankle sprain.

275
00:21:36.600 --> 00:21:40.040
Whatever's coming after
you. you're not gonna outrun it.

276
00:21:40.170 --> 00:21:41.260
That's for sure.

277
00:21:44.690 --> 00:21:46.546
I like reenie.

278
00:21:46.570 --> 00:21:47.790
She actually gives a crap.

279
00:21:49.570 --> 00:21:52.830
And I'm old enough to
remember that's a rare quality.

280
00:21:53.010 --> 00:21:54.750
But she shouldn't have gotten involved.

281
00:21:54.880 --> 00:21:56.360
Hold this right there.

282
00:21:56.530 --> 00:21:58.320
What's this have to
do with your testimony?

283
00:21:59.620 --> 00:22:01.670
Everything I said about that company

284
00:22:01.800 --> 00:22:03.630
was the god's honest truth.

285
00:22:03.760 --> 00:22:07.110
but this... isn't about that.

286
00:22:09.420 --> 00:22:10.810
Yeah. I gather that.

287
00:22:25.390 --> 00:22:27.016
- Sienna grimmer?
- Who are you?

288
00:22:27.040 --> 00:22:29.130
My name's reenie
Greene. I'm an attorney.

289
00:22:29.260 --> 00:22:30.806
I'm looking for your ex-husband.

290
00:22:30.830 --> 00:22:33.090
Wait. is kurtis missing. too?

291
00:22:34.440 --> 00:22:36.270
Yes. No one's seen him since yesterday.

292
00:22:36.400 --> 00:22:38.270
I know that you spoke
with him that morning.

293
00:22:38.400 --> 00:22:40.270
- You know anything about this?
- No.

294
00:22:40.400 --> 00:22:44.010
I'm sorry. Who else is missing?

295
00:22:50.540 --> 00:22:52.020
Your visitor here is from Louisiana.

296
00:22:57.070 --> 00:22:59.380
- Reenie. I got kurtis.
- Great.

297
00:23:02.640 --> 00:23:04.420
- Are you with Jackie?
- Who's Jackie?

298
00:23:04.560 --> 00:23:05.910
Stepdaughter.

299
00:23:06.040 --> 00:23:07.016
No. Why?

300
00:23:07.040 --> 00:23:08.610
She's missing.

301
00:23:08.740 --> 00:23:10.500
<i>I'm at your ex-wife's
house with the police.</i>

302
00:23:10.610 --> 00:23:12.546
<i>Look. she didn't turn up for work today.</i>

303
00:23:12.570 --> 00:23:14.440
Sienna went to her
place. but she's gone.

304
00:23:14.570 --> 00:23:15.676
I'm gonna kill them all.

305
00:23:15.700 --> 00:23:17.350
Who did this?

306
00:23:17.480 --> 00:23:19.220
Lowell Parker.

307
00:23:20.310 --> 00:23:22.230
Dixie mafia.

308
00:23:22.360 --> 00:23:24.710
Runs guns. drugs. anything
he can get his hands on.

309
00:23:24.880 --> 00:23:25.880
You work for him?

310
00:23:26.010 --> 00:23:27.970
Muscle.

311
00:23:28.100 --> 00:23:30.686
Long time ago.

312
00:23:30.710 --> 00:23:32.020
But I disappeared.

313
00:23:34.240 --> 00:23:37.070
Who died on a fishing trip.

314
00:23:37.200 --> 00:23:39.510
<i>Moved a few states over.</i>

315
00:23:39.640 --> 00:23:41.176
<i>Thought it was all behind me.</i>

316
00:23:41.200 --> 00:23:42.486
Well. why would he
take your stepdaughter

317
00:23:42.510 --> 00:23:43.916
after so many years?

318
00:23:43.940 --> 00:23:46.290
'Cause he found me. and
now he wants blood for blood.

319
00:23:46.430 --> 00:23:48.016
You agreeing to testify blew your cover.

320
00:23:48.040 --> 00:23:49.480
Has to be it.

321
00:23:49.600 --> 00:23:51.690
I never should've gotten
involved in that lawsuit.

322
00:23:53.210 --> 00:23:56.366
- I have to find Jackie.
- I can help you.

323
00:23:56.390 --> 00:23:58.496
All right. Grab your stuff. Let's go.

324
00:23:58.520 --> 00:23:59.650
Thanks. reenie.

325
00:24:04.970 --> 00:24:07.540
- Revenge.
- Revenge for what?

326
00:24:10.100 --> 00:24:12.100
Parker trusted me.

327
00:24:16.060 --> 00:24:17.930
She was a handful.

328
00:24:18.110 --> 00:24:19.786
Easy here.

329
00:24:19.810 --> 00:24:22.176
In and out of trouble.

330
00:24:22.200 --> 00:24:23.940
I mean. she was a sweet kid. but...

331
00:24:32.510 --> 00:24:35.080
But she was hooked on blues.

332
00:24:35.210 --> 00:24:37.870
And one day. I went to pick her up.

333
00:24:38.000 --> 00:24:39.780
and she was dead in the bathtub.

334
00:24:41.390 --> 00:24:42.610
Od'd.

335
00:24:42.740 --> 00:24:44.416
Blame you for that?

336
00:24:44.440 --> 00:24:47.880
Easier to blame me than her. I guess.

337
00:24:54.490 --> 00:24:55.750
We'll find her.

338
00:24:58.710 --> 00:25:00.410
<i>Kurtis isn't who we thought he was.</i>

339
00:25:00.540 --> 00:25:02.800
He was a bodyguard for lowell Parker.

340
00:25:02.940 --> 00:25:04.380
a Dixie mafia boss.

341
00:25:04.500 --> 00:25:06.580
So this has nothing to do
with praiter and Rockwell?

342
00:25:06.640 --> 00:25:08.860
No. I mean. they're not the
ones that came after him.

343
00:25:08.990 --> 00:25:11.210
And we made an
accusation in front of the judge

344
00:25:11.340 --> 00:25:12.340
that we can't support.

345
00:25:12.380 --> 00:25:15.250
Well. not necessarily.

346
00:25:15.430 --> 00:25:17.260
Parker was tipped somehow.

347
00:25:17.430 --> 00:25:20.480
and kurtis seems to think
that the lawsuit blew his cover.

348
00:25:20.610 --> 00:25:23.610
But his name was never public record.

349
00:25:23.740 --> 00:25:27.220
So. even if praiter and Rockwell
didn't commit the actual crime.

350
00:25:27.350 --> 00:25:29.050
someone must have
tapped the first domino.

351
00:25:29.220 --> 00:25:30.416
There's a mole.

352
00:25:30.440 --> 00:25:32.050
Yeah.

353
00:25:32.180 --> 00:25:33.726
But we have to put the whole thing

354
00:25:33.750 --> 00:25:35.620
on the back burner for now.

355
00:25:35.750 --> 00:25:38.110
Okay. just until we know that
kurtis's stepdaughter's safe.

356
00:25:38.190 --> 00:25:39.670
Okay.

357
00:25:42.580 --> 00:25:43.800
- Keep me posted.
- Will do.

358
00:25:48.460 --> 00:25:49.850
Hello?

359
00:25:49.980 --> 00:25:51.810
<i>Reenie Greene?</i>

360
00:25:51.990 --> 00:25:53.820
Who's this?

361
00:25:55.120 --> 00:25:56.470
Lowell Parker.

362
00:25:57.770 --> 00:26:01.030
- How'd you get this number?
- Does that really matter?

363
00:26:01.170 --> 00:26:04.130
No. it does not.

364
00:26:04.300 --> 00:26:07.960
What matters is I need this
to happen without the cops.

365
00:26:08.090 --> 00:26:10.050
You need what to happen exactly?

366
00:26:10.220 --> 00:26:14.260
<i>I was really hoping you
weren't gonna waste my time.</i>

367
00:26:16.010 --> 00:26:17.660
But just so you understand...

368
00:26:19.360 --> 00:26:21.320
Help me! Help me! Please
help me! Please help me!

369
00:26:25.930 --> 00:26:27.410
You do exactly what I say.

370
00:26:43.600 --> 00:26:45.016
- Hey.
- Hey.

371
00:26:45.040 --> 00:26:46.170
Sure you weren't followed?

372
00:26:46.340 --> 00:26:47.820
Yes. I stuck to the plan.

373
00:26:48.000 --> 00:26:51.090
Now. this is the location of the meet.

374
00:26:51.220 --> 00:26:54.270
Parker said that he wants
me to deliver kurtis personally.

375
00:26:54.400 --> 00:26:56.790
Then Jackie walks.

376
00:26:56.960 --> 00:26:58.660
- I don't trust it.
- I know.

377
00:26:58.790 --> 00:27:01.710
but the best way to minimize
risk and protect Jackie

378
00:27:01.840 --> 00:27:05.190
is to follow the ransom demands exactly.

379
00:27:05.320 --> 00:27:07.060
I don't want to mess around with this.

380
00:27:07.190 --> 00:27:08.930
It's my life for hers.

381
00:27:09.060 --> 00:27:10.216
And I'm okay with that.

382
00:27:10.240 --> 00:27:12.900
I'm on borrowed time anyway.

383
00:27:13.020 --> 00:27:15.240
If the last thing I do
is save Jackie. then...

384
00:27:15.370 --> 00:27:17.500
Then at least I've done something good.

385
00:27:34.390 --> 00:27:36.310
Okay. reenie's almost at the meet.

386
00:27:36.440 --> 00:27:37.806
Yeah. I know. I'm watching it. too.

387
00:27:37.830 --> 00:27:39.140
But come here. Check this out.

388
00:27:42.230 --> 00:27:43.580
My god. That's-that's him.

389
00:27:43.710 --> 00:27:45.450
That's the courier.

390
00:27:48.930 --> 00:27:50.110
Followed the local sales.

391
00:27:50.230 --> 00:27:51.710
Nice.

392
00:27:51.840 --> 00:27:53.540
Any connection to praiter and Rockwell?

393
00:28:01.420 --> 00:28:03.290
Well. he's got to fit in this somehow.

394
00:28:03.420 --> 00:28:05.616
Can I see his employment history?

395
00:28:05.640 --> 00:28:07.030
Certainly.

396
00:28:16.430 --> 00:28:21.050
Maybe... I think I got to call Maxine.

397
00:28:22.270 --> 00:28:23.750
Okay.

398
00:28:28.750 --> 00:28:29.930
We're almost there.

399
00:28:32.100 --> 00:28:33.840
Why are you doing this for me?

400
00:28:36.240 --> 00:28:37.720
I'm not a good man.

401
00:28:39.500 --> 00:28:41.370
Come on.

402
00:28:45.550 --> 00:28:47.510
You're a better man than you think.

403
00:28:47.640 --> 00:28:49.730
I was Parker's enforcer.

404
00:28:50.900 --> 00:28:52.820
The things I did...

405
00:28:53.910 --> 00:28:55.910
I didn't deserve the second chance I got.

406
00:28:59.220 --> 00:29:00.480
You know...

407
00:29:02.000 --> 00:29:03.896
the first time I ever
stepped into a courtroom.

408
00:29:03.920 --> 00:29:06.710
I was actually the defendant.

409
00:29:08.960 --> 00:29:11.140
Yeah. I know. I was 14 years old.

410
00:29:11.270 --> 00:29:13.840
Broke into a local department store

411
00:29:13.970 --> 00:29:16.630
and stole a beautiful Chanel clutch.

412
00:29:16.760 --> 00:29:19.150
It was worth thousands of dollars.

413
00:29:19.280 --> 00:29:20.280
Why?

414
00:29:22.720 --> 00:29:24.980
My sister dared me.

415
00:29:25.980 --> 00:29:27.380
It was just me and her at the time.

416
00:29:27.460 --> 00:29:28.640
We were on our own.

417
00:29:28.810 --> 00:29:30.136
You know. my dad was deployed out.

418
00:29:30.160 --> 00:29:33.120
My mom. she was basically absent.

419
00:29:34.820 --> 00:29:35.950
It was just something

420
00:29:36.080 --> 00:29:38.170
that we would never be able to afford.

421
00:29:39.600 --> 00:29:42.170
She said no one would
notice. no one would care.

422
00:29:43.520 --> 00:29:45.780
I just wanted to see if she was right.

423
00:29:47.570 --> 00:29:49.750
Anyway. point is. is that

424
00:29:49.880 --> 00:29:52.930
they assigned me this public defender.

425
00:29:53.050 --> 00:29:54.140
I'll never forget her.

426
00:29:55.400 --> 00:29:57.920
She said that. "life goes two ways.

427
00:29:58.060 --> 00:30:00.540
You're either the painter
or you're the paint."

428
00:30:09.940 --> 00:30:11.990
We choose who we are. you know?

429
00:30:16.950 --> 00:30:20.080
My real name's Eugene.

430
00:30:20.210 --> 00:30:24.520
Guys used to call me gene
gene the dancing machine.

431
00:30:27.260 --> 00:30:28.260
<i>Gong show?</i>

432
00:30:29.570 --> 00:30:31.010
Before your time.

433
00:30:32.790 --> 00:30:34.570
You liked to dance?

434
00:30:34.700 --> 00:30:36.180
No. the opposite.

435
00:30:39.620 --> 00:30:41.880
Okay.

436
00:30:42.010 --> 00:30:44.100
I may just stick with kurtis. then.

437
00:30:50.890 --> 00:30:53.150
Right.

438
00:30:56.250 --> 00:30:57.250
You ready?

439
00:30:57.330 --> 00:30:59.070
Here we go.

440
00:31:16.610 --> 00:31:18.610
<i>Car just pulled up. Two occupants.</i>

441
00:31:27.710 --> 00:31:29.476
All I care about is that
she gets out of this.

442
00:31:29.500 --> 00:31:30.386
You watch your back.

443
00:31:30.410 --> 00:31:31.720
Kurtis?

444
00:31:31.850 --> 00:31:33.070
Let's go.

445
00:31:45.250 --> 00:31:46.250
Hands on the wheel.

446
00:32:23.460 --> 00:32:24.460
Jackie.

447
00:32:28.820 --> 00:32:30.390
You look like hell. gene.

448
00:32:30.560 --> 00:32:32.040
Let her go.

449
00:32:36.260 --> 00:32:37.830
Do whatever you want with me.

450
00:32:37.960 --> 00:32:40.716
I can't let you off that easy.

451
00:32:40.740 --> 00:32:42.180
We had a deal.

452
00:32:51.060 --> 00:32:53.256
I didn't have that choice.

453
00:32:53.280 --> 00:32:57.850
I gave you the most important
job. and you screwed it up.

454
00:32:57.980 --> 00:33:00.240
My daughter's dead...

455
00:33:04.590 --> 00:33:06.330
because you dropped the ball.

456
00:33:09.070 --> 00:33:12.576
Now you're gonna get to see
what I do to somebody you love.

457
00:33:12.600 --> 00:33:15.560
I'm begging you. lowell. Please.

458
00:33:37.540 --> 00:33:39.060
No!

459
00:33:53.640 --> 00:33:54.640
No. no. no. no!

460
00:34:00.690 --> 00:34:03.300
Still got a lot of fight in you. old man?

461
00:34:29.420 --> 00:34:33.080
Maybe we need to help
nature along a little bit.

462
00:34:37.600 --> 00:34:41.910
But I want you to see something
before your number's up.

463
00:35:16.030 --> 00:35:17.080
Behind the car!

464
00:35:26.520 --> 00:35:27.700
Hey!

465
00:35:29.740 --> 00:35:32.090
- Come here. You all right?
- Thank you.

466
00:35:32.220 --> 00:35:34.000
Yeah?

467
00:35:34.130 --> 00:35:35.260
Jackie.

468
00:35:35.440 --> 00:35:37.230
- Hi. I'm here. I'm okay.
- Jackie.

469
00:35:38.050 --> 00:35:39.490
I'm okay.

470
00:35:39.660 --> 00:35:42.050
- Easy. now. Take it easy.
- Is he gonna be okay?

471
00:35:42.180 --> 00:35:44.620
- Just needs an ambulance.
- Stay with us. kurtis.

472
00:35:56.370 --> 00:35:58.110
Thanks. kurtis. We'll see you soon.

473
00:36:00.590 --> 00:36:01.566
- Hey.
- Hey.

474
00:36:01.590 --> 00:36:03.640
That was kurtis. He is relentless.

475
00:36:03.810 --> 00:36:06.136
He wants to testify as soon
as the hospital discharges him.

476
00:36:06.160 --> 00:36:08.640
Ooh. a man after my own heart.

477
00:36:08.780 --> 00:36:12.310
And here comes the fun part.

478
00:36:14.520 --> 00:36:16.520
Everything.

479
00:36:18.260 --> 00:36:19.806
We can save the high school
games for the courtroom.

480
00:36:19.830 --> 00:36:21.230
You're not gonna be a part of that.

481
00:36:21.350 --> 00:36:22.596
Shame.

482
00:36:22.620 --> 00:36:24.540
Unless you have
something important to share.

483
00:36:24.660 --> 00:36:27.750
- I'm late to meet my wife.
- Actually. Devin.

484
00:36:27.880 --> 00:36:29.660
Quick question for you.

485
00:36:29.800 --> 00:36:32.500
You were a summer associate at
Danvers and saperstein. correct?

486
00:36:34.580 --> 00:36:36.320
I was.

487
00:36:36.460 --> 00:36:37.346
Out of their New Orleans office. yes?

488
00:36:37.370 --> 00:36:38.630
Yeah.

489
00:36:38.760 --> 00:36:41.590
And that's the same firm
who represents lowell Parker

490
00:36:41.720 --> 00:36:43.030
on rico charges?

491
00:36:43.160 --> 00:36:45.240
- What's this about?
- We're hoping you can tell us.

492
00:36:49.860 --> 00:36:52.430
'Cause that firm employed
the courier who delivered

493
00:36:52.560 --> 00:36:53.966
some pretty interesting
photographs of us

494
00:36:53.990 --> 00:36:55.316
to our offices.

495
00:36:55.340 --> 00:36:56.860
Take your time. Devin.

496
00:36:57.000 --> 00:36:59.660
I keep forgetting you failed
the bar. what was it. five times?

497
00:36:59.780 --> 00:37:00.780
Five times?

498
00:37:01.960 --> 00:37:03.416
I just don't know what
you're talking about.

499
00:37:03.440 --> 00:37:04.846
But I bet you do.

500
00:37:04.870 --> 00:37:07.700
If you need it spelled out
for you. I can help you out.

501
00:37:07.830 --> 00:37:09.570
It was you who gave up kurtis.

502
00:37:09.710 --> 00:37:11.320
Ring a bell now?

503
00:37:11.450 --> 00:37:13.076
You recognized him.
served him up to Parker.

504
00:37:13.100 --> 00:37:14.710
For what? Money? An old favor?

505
00:37:14.880 --> 00:37:16.230
I don't know exactly.

506
00:37:16.360 --> 00:37:18.126
but I'm pretty sure this
is the end of your career.

507
00:37:18.150 --> 00:37:19.500
You're speculating.

508
00:37:19.630 --> 00:37:21.460
I don't speculate.

509
00:37:25.420 --> 00:37:26.680
What do you want?

510
00:37:26.810 --> 00:37:28.510
Justice.

511
00:37:28.640 --> 00:37:30.876
For every single person that
praiter and Rockwell wronged.

512
00:37:30.900 --> 00:37:32.510
Starting with a favorable settlement

513
00:37:32.640 --> 00:37:35.226
in our in boxes no later
than tomorrow morning.

514
00:37:35.250 --> 00:37:36.470
Why would I do that?

515
00:37:36.600 --> 00:37:38.120
Because we can drop this whole thing

516
00:37:38.300 --> 00:37:40.560
to the bar association right now.

517
00:37:40.690 --> 00:37:44.130
Or we could give you
a few weeks. you know.

518
00:37:50.140 --> 00:37:51.710
Best and only deal.

519
00:37:55.450 --> 00:37:57.150
I'll start drafting it now.

520
00:38:01.630 --> 00:38:05.200
<i>It's just harder than it looks.</i>

521
00:38:09.030 --> 00:38:11.266
Something like that. okay?

522
00:38:11.290 --> 00:38:13.550
Nice and relaxed.

523
